content: Use this space to discuss the relative merits and demerits of each plan from your assigned perspective in step 2. That was the step where you were asked to write an individual proposal and post it to the discussion forum. Work towards a consensus on which plan you think is the best as a group. Wherever possible, supplement plan suggestions, agreements and disagreements with reasons, and try to refer to or build upon your teammates' ideas.
I believe Plan 2 would be the best plan to implement
I think Plan 2 is best as well
While out of the budget it is renewable and will save money in the long rung with no greenhouse gases and waste costs
I agree. Only option to stay under budget would require too much dependance on coal which would be bad environmentally
I'm here. I also think plan 2.
It isn't exactly the plan I proposed, but with 60 percent renewable energy, it is a good plan.
Yeah and they want to be green plus the wind mills don't require much maintenance
I was leaning more towards hydro power, but with Plan 2 there is a good balance. If there should be a drought, the other resources will cover for the loss of water resource.
I was leaning towards water as well but considering the cost I believe wind is best in this case
Have we done everything needed to finish this?
If you guys like it I'm good
I'm good... just double checking to see if we can beef it up a bit
It says to write the proposal on the Etherpad. Do we need to write a formal proposal?

cause at the top it says it's our proposal

Thank you for participating in the discussion. You now have just 5 minutes to finalize a joint argument in favor of one plan and complete your proposal on the left. Keep in mind that you will be evaluated solely based on the quality of your proposal (i.e., the thoroughness of the reasoning displayed).
